You are designing a multi-functional KitchenRobot for a technology company. This robot has different capabilities: chopping vegetables, stirring soup, and kneading dough.

You are asked to convert these operations into Command objects. This way, instead of waiting at the robot, the user can queue commands or undo the last action with a single button press.

Requirements:

Receiver: Create the KitchenRobot class. It should contain the chopVegetables(), stirSoup(), and kneadDough() methods.

Command Interface: Define the iCommand interface. It should contain the execute() and undo() methods.

Concrete Commands:

ChopCommand (Vegetable chopping command)

StirCommand (Soup stirring command)

Invoker: Write the RobotController class. This class should:

Be able to accept a command object (setCommand).

It must be able to execute the command (executeCommand).

It must be able to undo the last executed command (undoCommand).

Main (Test): Create a food processor, chop vegetables in it, then undo the operation.